{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Out of the depths I have cried to you, Yahweh."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Lord, hear my voice. Let your ears be attentive to the voice of my petitions."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "If you, Yah, kept a record of sins, Lord, who could st and?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "But there is forgiveness with you, therefore you are feared."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I wait for Yahweh. My soul waits."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "I hope in his word."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "My soul longs for the Lord more than watchmen long for the morning, more than watchmen for the morning."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Israel, hope in Yahweh, for there is loving kindness with Yahweh."
        },
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "Abundant redemption is with him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "hymnal",
          "text": "He will redeem Israel from all their sins."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}